  "title": "Customer Support Service Officer (Rotating Day Shifts - AM/PM) - 1 Year @ Yio Chu Kang",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Manage front counter operations, including handling bookings, reservations, and general customer enquiries</p></li><li><p>Provide courteous and efficient customer service to facility users and visitors</p></li><li><p>Perform routine facility checks and basic reporting in accordance with operational procedures</p></li><li><p>Assist in setting up and moving equipment such as tables, chairs, and sports or recreational items as required</p></li><li><p>Support daily facilities and recreational operations by following work instructions and standard operating procedures</p></li><li><p>Use basic computer applications (MS Office, email, booking systems) for data entry and administrative tasks</p></li><li><p>Work rotating shifts, including weekends and public holidays, as required</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>2 years’ experience in customer service</strong>, or at least <strong>6 months’ experience</strong> in recreational or facilities operations</p></li><li><p>Physically fit and able to handle manual tasks involving lifting and moving equipment</p></li><li><p>Basic proficiency in <strong>MS Office applications</strong> and booking or reservation systems</p></li><li><p>Customer-oriented, dependable, and able to work well in a team environment</p></li><li><p>Willingness to work <strong>rotating shifts</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>GCE ‘N’ Level / ‘O’ Level or equivalent</strong></p></li><li><p>No formal certification required; <strong>relevant experience will be prioritised</strong></p></li></ul>",
